![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/31258d46-d48a-4a3e-979c-9a15074c6e5e/20240413_122444.jpg)

Bodyslam.net has reported that Jon Moxley has been granted time off from AEW in order to fulfill his responsibilities as the IWGP World Heavyweight Champion. This move emphasizes the collaborative nature between AEW and New Japan Pro-Wrestling.

Moxley's upcoming schedule includes appearances at the upcoming Dontaku and Kizuna Road shows, as well as the highly anticipated Dominion event in Osaka, Japan.

Furthermore, it was revealed that Ren Narita of the House of Torture faction will be Moxley's first challenger for the championship. This sets the stage for an intense showdown between two formidable competitors, adding an extra layer of anticipation to Moxley's upcoming matches.

Overall, Moxley's time off from AEW underscores the growing cooperation between wrestling promotions and promises thrilling matchups for fans in the near future.